    All Classes and Interfaces

    Class
    Description
    Account
    Represents an abstract account in the system.
    Administrator
    Represents an Administrator account in the system.
    AdministratorController
    This is the Administrator Controller that handles all the logic for the Administrator account's possible actions.
    Appointment
    Represents an appointment in the hospital management system.
    Appointment.AppointmentStatus
    Enum representing the status of an appointment.
    AppointmentController
    Controller class to manage appointments, doctor unavailability, and appointment outcomes.
    AppOutcome
    Represents the outcome of an appointment.
    CSVUtilsController
    Controller class implementing CSVUtilsInterface for managing CSV data storage and retrieval for users, staff, patients, and medicines in the Hospital Management System.
    CSVUtilsInterface
    Interface defining methods for CSV data handling in the Hospital Management System.
    Doctor
    Doctor class which inherits from Staff class.
    DoctorController
    The DoctorController class manages the interaction between a logged-in Doctor and the system, comprising the logic for handling the following features available to the Doctor: 1.
    IMedicalRecordService
    Interface for managing medical records.
    MainMenuController
    Main controller for the Hospital Management System (HMS).
    MedicalRecord
    Represents a patient's medical record, containing personal details and a history of diagnoses and treatments.
    MedicalRecordRepo
    Repository class for handling medical record data.
    MedicalRecordService
    Service class responsible for handling medical record operations, including retrieving, updating contact information, and updating diagnoses and treatments.
    Medicine
    Represents a medicine in the hospital management system.
    PasswordUtilsController
    Handles password-related functionality, including hashing, validation, and first-time login handling.
    PasswordUtilsInterface
    Interface defining utility methods for password management in the Hospital Management System.
    Patient
    Represents a patient account in the system.
    PatientController
    The PatientController class manages the interaction between a logged-in patient and the system, allowing the patient to perform various actions such as viewing medical records, updating contact details, scheduling/rescheduling/canceling appointments, and checking doctor availability.
    Pharmacist
    Pharmacist class which inherits from Staff class.
    PharmacistController
    The PharmacistController class manages the interaction between a logged-in patient and the system, comprising the logic for handling the following features available to the pharmacist: 1.
    ReplenishmentRequest
    Represents a replenishment request for a specific medicine.
    ReplenishmentRequest.ReplenishmentStatus
    Enum representing the possible statuses of a replenishment request.
    Staff
    Represents a staff member in the hospital management system.
    Unavailability
    Represents a doctor's unavailability for appointments.
